Sure! Here’s a simple CSS code snippet to style a button with a bright green background and white text:

```css
.bright-green-button {
  background-color: #39FF14; /* Bright green */
  color: white;
  border: none;
  padding: 12px 24px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 16px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0, 255, 20, 0.2);
}

.bright-green-button:hover {
  background-color: #27FF09; /* Slightly darker green on hover */
}
```

**HTML Example:**

```html
<button class="bright-green-button">Click Me!</button>
```

You can adjust the shade of green (`#39FF14`) to your preference for "bright green." This code also includes some basic button styling for a nice look and feel.

